data.Name: Lil Mosey
data.Bio: Lathan Moses Echols (born January 25, 2002), known professionally as Lil Mosey, is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter. He first gained mainstream success with his song "Noticed", which peaked at #80 on the Billboard Hot 100. He dropped his debut mixtape Northsbest in 2018, which was eventually certified Gold.
